name: Air Canada 767-333ER Cleans the Runway on Takeoff from Calgary
description:
Happy Heavy Aircraft Friday!
Here's an Air Canada Boeing 767-300ER departing Calgary International Airport for Tokyo/Narita for all of you! The spool-up sound from the 767s is just awesome! He sure cleaned the runway! This is another one of my older videos, and sorry for the shakiness, I didn't have my tripod. I hope you enjoy!

Thanks for watching, please comment, rate, and subscribe! More videos are coming soon.
